Description:
Fez - an indie game developed by the independent studio Polytron Corporation. It was initially announced its creator , Phil Fisch , TIGSource.com on July 17, 2007 . At later stages of development has been shown in Ã‚Â«Indie Game: The MovieÃ‚Â». The plot revolves around a two-dimensional man named Gomez, who lives in a village in the 2D- world.Gomez once met a three-dimensional object - cube , from which he received a gift of magic fez wearing that get the opportunity to feel the third dimension. When Gomez begins to explore his new capacity, Cube suddenly explodes , and then a two-dimensional world began to falter , and after, and all dependent.
The game restarts and Gomez wakes up to discover that he can now explore the world in three dimensions. Now the main character to collect all the fragments of the exploded Hypercube , which were scattered around the world before the world will be broken off into pieces.

Features:
The main objective of Fez - collect 32 cubes that are scattered around the world , in order to restore and save the Hypercube Gomez homeworld from destruction. Cuba and fragments thereof are visible and can be assembled by simply moving them.

Fez is presented in the form of a 2D- platformer in which Gomez can walk, jump, climb , and manipulate objects . Nevertheless, the player may at any time shift perspective world rotating by 90 degrees relative to the screen .

Fez has received the award &quot; Excellence in Visual Art&quot; at the Independent Games Festival in 2008 , which also was nominated for &quot; Design Innovation&quot; .

